    <div class="proj-details col s3 offset-s1">
      <h5 class="col-head">ABOUT</h5>
      <p class="col-para">
        TrueTrac is for people who enjoy the outdoors and want a way to mark where they have been but also learn where other like-minded people like to go. It features a chat-room so that users can spill their secrets as which spots are great for camping, hiking, 4WD, etc.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="proj-details col s2 offset-s1">
      <h5 class="col-head">TECH</h5>
      <ul class="col-para">
        <li>JavaScript/jQuery</li>
        <li>Google Maps API/Custom API</li>
        <li>Ruby on Rails</li>
        <li>OAuth2(OmniAuth)</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL</li>
        <li>HTML5/CSS3</li>
        <li>Materialize</li>
        <li>Github/Heroku</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="proj-details col s3 offset-s1">
      <h5 class="col-head">PROCESS</h5>
      <p class="col-para">
        At the heart of TrueTrac is a Ruby on Rails application, designed to tie in my love of the outdoors and coding. The application still has a little while to go before I can call it v1.0 but I have so far enjoyed the challenge of building it.
      </p>
